## How to Set Up and Run

### Step 1: Database Setup
1. Create a MySQL database named `e_commerce_db`.
2. Run the schema script: [schema.sql](file:///d:/node/E-Commerce-web/backend/database/schema.sql)
3. (Optional) Populate initial data: [seed.sql](file:///d:/node/E-Commerce-web/backend/database/seed.sql)

### Step 2: Configuration
1. Initialize the environment variables by creating a `.env` file in the `backend/` folder based on [.env.example](file:///d:/node/E-Commerce-web/backend/.env.example).
2. Set your DB credentials and `JWT_SECRET`.

### Step 3: Start the Backend
Open a terminal in the `backend/` directory and run:
```bash
npm install
node server.js
```

